Note that most absorption check for exponential strongest proofdoors failed for insufficient memory or timeout. What's left are very likely the borderline exponential families.
That being said, the absorption heatmaps of proofdoors of McMillan interpolants are sufficient to witness that CDCL solver failed to incrementally absorb the I_m and I_s over the majority of exponential formulas. If it fail to absorb the I_m then it cannot absorb I_s, as the contra-positive has been proved in appendix.